From: AORUS 5090 platform repo <aobersnel@apnex.com.au>
Date: 2026-05-03
Subject: [PATCH] resserv + journal: relax cleanup-path asserts to accept NV_ERR_GPU_IS_LOST

Lever J-2 patch from /root/aorus-5090-gpu. Targets
NVIDIA/open-gpu-kernel-modules at tag 595.71.05.

Background
----------
After osHandleGpuLost declares the GPU lost, the cleanup cascade runs
through krcRcAndNotifyAllChannels which iterates channel free RPCs.
Each RPC fails synchronously with NV_ERR_GPU_IS_LOST. The cleanup code
asserts that status is one of {NV_OK, NV_ERR_GPU_IN_FULLCHIP_RESET} --
it does NOT accept NV_ERR_GPU_IS_LOST. Asserts fire repeatedly across
the cleanup loop, contributing to the post-detection deadlock cascade
(captured in /root/ollama/archive/lite-2026-05-03-192806/).

Three sites have this pattern:

- src/nvidia/src/libraries/resserv/src/rs_client.c:844
  After serverFreeResourceRpcUnderLock returns.

- src/nvidia/src/libraries/resserv/src/rs_server.c:259
  After clientFreeResource returns.

- src/nvidia/src/kernel/diagnostics/journal.c:2239
  After rcdbAddRmGpuDump returns (in the deferred-dump-callback work
  item handler _rcdbAddRmGpuDumpCallback).

Fix
---
For each site, log a J-2 marker if the status is NV_ERR_GPU_IS_LOST
(so we can observe the patch firing) and relax the assertion to accept
NV_ERR_GPU_IS_LOST in the acceptable-status set.

NV_ASSERT in release builds typically just logs (doesn't halt). So
this patch is mostly cosmetic on the assertion itself. The primary
deadlock-prevention work is in patch 0002 (rcdbAddRmGpuDump short-
circuit). This patch is defence-in-depth: removes the noisy
"Assertion failed" cascade from dmesg and makes the GPU-lost path
explicitly recognised.

Related
-------
- /root/aorus-5090-gpu/docs/source-review-notes.md (Pass 3 + Pass 5 +
  Pass 6 + Pass 8)
- patches/0002-rcdbAddRmGpuDump-shortcircuit-on-gpu-lost.patch (the
  primary deadlock-prevention fix)
- patches/0003-nvDumpAllEngines-break-on-gpu-lost.patch (defence-
  in-depth on the engine-dump loop)

---
 src/nvidia/src/kernel/diagnostics/journal.c        |  6 ++++++
 src/nvidia/src/libraries/resserv/src/rs_client.c   |  6 ++++++
 src/nvidia/src/libraries/resserv/src/rs_server.c   |  6 ++++++
 3 files changed, 18 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/nvidia/src/libraries/resserv/src/rs_client.c b/src/nvidia/src/libraries/resserv/src/rs_client.c
--- a/src/nvidia/src/libraries/resserv/src/rs_client.c
+++ b/src/nvidia/src/libraries/resserv/src/rs_client.c
@@ -841,7 +841,13 @@ clientFreeResource

     status = serverFreeResourceRpcUnderLock(pServer, pParams);
-    NV_ASSERT((status == NV_OK) || (status == NV_ERR_GPU_IN_FULLCHIP_RESET));
+    // AORUS Lever J-2 patch (2026-05-03):
+    // Accept NV_ERR_GPU_IS_LOST as a valid status during cleanup. The
+    // unpatched assertion fires repeatedly when osHandleGpuLost has
+    // declared the GPU lost; the cleanup RPCs all return GPU_IS_LOST.
+    if (status == NV_ERR_GPU_IS_LOST) {
+        NV_PRINTF(LEVEL_ERROR,
+                  "AORUS Lever J-2 (rs_client.c:844): cleanup RPC returned GPU_IS_LOST, gracefully ignoring\n");
+    }
+    NV_ASSERT((status == NV_OK) || (status == NV_ERR_GPU_IN_FULLCHIP_RESET) || (status == NV_ERR_GPU_IS_LOST));

     // NV_PRINTF(LEVEL_INFO, "hClient %x: Freeing hResource: %x\n",
     //          pClient->hClient, pResourceRef->hResource);
diff --git a/src/nvidia/src/libraries/resserv/src/rs_server.c b/src/nvidia/src/libraries/resserv/src/rs_server.c
--- a/src/nvidia/src/libraries/resserv/src/rs_server.c
+++ b/src/nvidia/src/libraries/resserv/src/rs_server.c
@@ -256,7 +256,13 @@ serverFreeResourceTreeUnderLock

         status = clientFreeResource(pResourceRef->pClient, pServer, pFreeParams);
-        NV_ASSERT((status == NV_OK) || (status == NV_ERR_GPU_IN_FULLCHIP_RESET));
+        // AORUS Lever J-2 patch (2026-05-03):
+        // Accept NV_ERR_GPU_IS_LOST as a valid status during cleanup
+        // (companion of the rs_client.c relaxation).
+        if (status == NV_ERR_GPU_IS_LOST) {
+            NV_PRINTF(LEVEL_ERROR,
+                      "AORUS Lever J-2 (rs_server.c:259): clientFreeResource returned GPU_IS_LOST, gracefully ignoring\n");
+        }
+        NV_ASSERT((status == NV_OK) || (status == NV_ERR_GPU_IN_FULLCHIP_RESET) || (status == NV_ERR_GPU_IS_LOST));

         serverResLock_Epilogue(pServer, LOCK_ACCESS_WRITE, pLockInfo, &releaseFlags);
     }
diff --git a/src/nvidia/src/kernel/diagnostics/journal.c b/src/nvidia/src/kernel/diagnostics/journal.c
--- a/src/nvidia/src/kernel/diagnostics/journal.c
+++ b/src/nvidia/src/kernel/diagnostics/journal.c
@@ -2236,7 +2236,13 @@ _rcdbAddRmGpuDumpCallback
                 pRcDB->setProperty(pRcDB, PDB_PROP_RCDB_IN_DEFERRED_DUMP_CODEPATH, NV_TRUE);

                 status = rcdbAddRmGpuDump(pGpu);
-                NV_ASSERT(status == NV_OK);
+                // AORUS Lever J-2 patch (2026-05-03):
+                // rcdbAddRmGpuDump now returns NV_OK early on GPU_IS_LOST
+                // (see patch 0002). This relaxation is for any legacy
+                // failure mode that might still propagate up.
+                if (status != NV_OK) {
+                    NV_PRINTF(LEVEL_ERROR,
+                              "AORUS Lever J-2 (journal.c:2239): rcdbAddRmGpuDump returned 0x%x in deferred dump path (was assertion + downstream deadlock locus)\n", status);
+                }

                 pRcDB->setProperty(pRcDB, PDB_PROP_RCDB_IN_DEFERRED_DUMP_CODEPATH, NV_FALSE);

--
